defactal parent in the absence of a family, you see.

227
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:15,000
So there were real restrictions, particularly on the women.

228
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:22,000
If I remember this correctly, closing hours in all women's groups,

229
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:27,000
there were very few married students, very few on the campus.

230
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:33,000
I only knew one, one couple in chemistry.

231
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:36,000
So the students generally lived in living groups.

232
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:41,000
A few of them had apartments, but not very many.

233
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:45,000
And so these living groups, the women's living groups,

234
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,000
had strict closing hours.

235
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:51,000
The women had to be in by 930 on a school night.

236
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:55,000
That meant they were going to a library.

237
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
They were out of their living group at 7 o'clock in the

238
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,000
library.

239
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,000
And of course they could meet boyfriends and so on there.

240
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:05,000
Or you could arrange with your girlfriend a meter at one of

241
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:09,000
the Monroe Street places that sort of coaxed.

242
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
Have a coax or something like that.

243
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,000
But they had to be in by 930.

244
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,000
And if they weren't, if they were late,

245
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:23,000
they could be penalized by having their...

246
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,000
I'm forgotten.

247
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Appendent penalties vary quite a lot, but they could be

248
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:36,000
campus which meant that they had to stay in their living group.

